**Approach**
**1. Brute Force**
(a) - You can use 3 nested loops 
(b) - For checking rows,column and box seperately.

**2. Using a Single loop**
(a) - Make vectors of sets.
(b) - Each vector contain 9 sets. i.e, *9 set for rows, 9 set for column & 9 for box.*
(c) - Check if element is present in the box or not.
(d) - If Present, **return false**.
(e) - If Not Present, insert it into set and check for next element.

