# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We need to find p and q in the tree, and move upward until we discover where the two paths meet. This goes bottom to top, which means we need to do some bookkeeping. 
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Create a map from each node's value to that node's parent. Call this map **parents**. It will be populated depth first.
2. Follow the line of parents from **p**, and insert each of them into the set **p_ancestors**.
3. Follow the line of parents from **q**, until one is a member of **p_ancestors**. Return this node.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n) for an n-node tree. We traverse the entire tree to find each node and record its parents. We use this information to trace the path from **p** to root (O(1) lookup per node), and then from **q** to the lowest common ancestor node (also O(1) lookup per node).
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n) for an n-node tree. We create the **parents** map with n entries; we also create the set **pAncestors**, with a maximum of n members.
# Code (Java)
```
/**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * public class TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode left;
 *     TreeNode right;
 *     TreeNode(int x) { val = x; }
 * }
 */
class Solution {
        Map<Integer, TreeNode> parents;     // Parent node, by current node's value
        Set<Integer> pAncestors;            // A set for p's ancestors

    /**
        The constructor sets up parents and pAncestors.
     */
    public Solution() {
        parents = new HashMap<Integer, TreeNode>();
        pAncestors = new HashSet<Integer>();
    }

    /**
      Traverse the tree depth-first, finding the parent of each node and
      saving it to parents, recursively.

      @param node the starting node
     */
    private void findAllParents(TreeNode node) {
        if (node.left != null) {
            parents.put(node.left.val, node);
            findAllParents(node.left);
        }
        if (node.right != null) {
            parents.put(node.right.val, node);
            findAllParents(node.right);
        }
    }

    /**
        Traverse tree, depth first:
            At each node record its parent to the parents dictionary
        Follow the line of parents from p, and insert all into the set p_ancestors
